    (b) The contents, structure, layers, configuration, build process,
        or composition of any Container Artifacts, including but not
        limited to Docker images, Dockerfiles, image layers, base images,
        environment variables, build arguments, or any other artifacts
        used to construct or describe such containers;
    (c) Any trade secrets, proprietary methods, or confidential information
        embodied in or associated with the Software or Container Artifacts.

This prohibition applies regardless of the technical means used, including
but not limited to the use of debugging tools, disassemblers, decompilers,
container inspection tools (such as `docker history`, `docker inspect`,
`dive`, `skopeo`, or equivalent), layer extraction tools, binary analysis
tools, or any automated or manual analysis techniques.

This prohibition does not apply to the extent that such activity is
expressly required to be permitted by applicable law notwithstanding this
contractual limitation. Where applicable law permits such activity only
upon request to the Licensor, You shall first contact Licensor in writing
and provide a reasonable opportunity to address Your stated need before
engaging in any such activity.

